Database migrations (Alembic)
=============================

The database schema is managed with Alembic. The connection URL is taken from
the DATABASE_URL environment variable (see backend/config.py and
migrations/env.py); it falls back to the local SQLite file when unset.

Common commands (run from the project root):

  # Apply all pending migrations (run this on deploy, before starting the app)
  python -m alembic upgrade head

  # Autogenerate a new migration after changing a model in backend/models/
  python -m alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe your change"

  # Inspect state / history
  python -m alembic current
  python -m alembic history

  # Roll back the most recent migration
  python -m alembic downgrade -1

Notes
-----
* In production the app does NOT create tables itself - run
  `alembic upgrade head` first. Locally (ENVIRONMENT != production) the app
  still calls create_all() for convenience, so Alembic is optional in dev.
* Always review autogenerated migrations before committing - Alembic does not
  detect every change (e.g. some constraint/enum edits) perfectly.
* SQLite uses batch mode (render_as_batch) so ALTER TABLE-style changes work.
